@page "/privacy"

<PageTitle>Privacy Policy - Contoso Risk Analysis Platform</PageTitle>

<div class="info-page">
    <div class="info-container">
        <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
        
        <div class="info-section">
            <p class="last-updated">Last Updated: January 2025</p>
        </div>

        <div class="info-section">
            <h2>Overview</h2>
            <p>
                This Privacy Policy describes how the Contoso Risk Analysis Platform ("CRAP", "we", "our", or "us") 
                handles information when you use our demonstration platform. This is a demo project created for 
                educational purposes and is not a commercial product.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="info-section">
            <h2>Information Collection</h2>
            <p>
                As a demonstration platform, we collect minimal information necessary for the application to function:
            </p>
            <ul class="feature-list">
                <li><strong>Chat Messages:</strong> Your queries and conversations with the AI agent are processed to provide responses</li>
                <li><strong>Document Content:</strong> PDF documents you upload are processed for text extraction and analysis</li>
                <li><strong>Session Data:</strong> Conversation IDs and thread IDs to maintain context across messages</li>
                <li><strong>Technical Data:</strong> Basic telemetry and error logs via Azure Application Insights for debugging</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="info-section">
            <h2>How We Use Information</h2>
            <p>Information collected is used solely for:</p>
            <ul class="feature-list">
                <li>Processing your risk assessment queries and providing AI-generated responses</li>
                <li>Maintaining conversation context within your session</li>
                <li>Indexing document content in Elasticsearch for semantic search</li>
                <li>Monitoring application performance and diagnosing technical issues</li>
                <li>Improving the demo platform's functionality</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="info-section">
            <h2>Data Storage</h2>
            <p>
                Data processed by the platform is stored in the following services:
            </p>
            <ul class="feature-list">
                <li><strong>Elasticsearch:</strong> Document chunks and metadata for search functionality</li>
                <li><strong>Azure AI Foundry:</strong> Conversation threads and agent state</li>
                <li><strong>Application Insights:</strong> Telemetry and diagnostic logs</li>
            </ul>
            <p>
                All data is stored in accordance with the security and privacy standards of Microsoft Azure 
                and Elastic Cloud services.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="info-section">
            <h2>Data Sharing</h2>
            <p>
                We do not sell, trade, or otherwise transfer your information to third parties. Your data is 
                processed by the following service providers as necessary for platform functionality:
            </p>
            <ul class="feature-list">
                <li><strong>Microsoft Azure:</strong> Provides AI, compute, and storage services</li>
                <li><strong>Elastic:</strong> Provides search and analytics capabilities</li>
            </ul>
            <p>
                These services are bound by their respective privacy policies and data processing agreements.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="info-section">
            <h2>Content Safety</h2>
            <p>
                The platform includes Azure Content Safety integration to detect and filter potentially harmful 
                content. This includes:
            </p>
            <ul class="feature-list">
                <li>Jailbreak attempt detection to prevent misuse of AI capabilities</li>
                <li>Content moderation for inappropriate material</li>
                <li>Configurable detection modes (Disabled, Audit, or Enforce)</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="info-section">
            <h2>Your Rights</h2>
            <p>
                As this is a demonstration platform, data retention and user rights are limited. However, 
                if you deploy your own instance using the open-source code, you have full control over:
            </p>
            <ul class="feature-list">
                <li>Data collection and retention policies</li>
                <li>Access controls and authentication</li>
                <li>Data deletion and export capabilities</li>
                <li>Compliance with relevant privacy regulations (GDPR, CCPA, etc.)</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="info-section">
            <h2>Security</h2>
            <p>
                The platform uses industry-standard security practices:
            </p>
            <ul class="feature-list">
                <li>HTTPS encryption for all data transmission</li>
                <li>Azure managed identities for secure service-to-service authentication</li>
                <li>API keys and secrets stored securely in Azure configuration</li>
                <li>Content safety checks to prevent malicious usage</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="info-section">
            <h2>Analytics</h2>
            <p>
                The platform uses Microsoft Clarity for web analytics to understand user behavior and 
                improve the user experience. Clarity collects anonymous usage data including:
            </p>
            <ul class="feature-list">
                <li>Page views and navigation patterns</li>
                <li>Mouse movements and click behavior</li>
                <li>Session recordings (anonymized)</li>
            </ul>
            <p>
                For more information, see the 
                <a href="https://privacy.microsoft.com/en-us/privacystatement" target="_blank">Microsoft Privacy Statement</a>.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="info-section">
            <h2>Open Source Project</h2>
            <p>
                This is an open-source demonstration project. The complete source code is available on 
                GitHub, allowing you to review exactly how data is handled. You can deploy your own instance 
                with full control over data processing and privacy settings.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="info-section">
            <h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>
            <p>
                As this is a demo project, this Privacy Policy may be updated to reflect changes in 
                functionality or to comply with evolving standards. Check the GitHub repository for 
                the latest version.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="info-section">
            <h2>Contact Information</h2>
            <p>
                For questions about this Privacy Policy or the platform's data handling practices, 
                please visit the GitHub repository or contact the project creator:
            </p>
            <ul class="feature-list">
                <li><strong>GitHub:</strong> <a href="https://github.com/michaelsrichter/azure-elastic-risk-agent" target="_blank">azure-elastic-risk-agent</a></li>
                <li><strong>Creator:</strong> <a href="https://aka.ms/mrichter" target="_blank">Mike Richter</a></li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="info-section">
            <h2>Disclaimer</h2>
            <p>
                This is a demonstration platform for educational purposes. It should not be used for 
                processing sensitive or confidential information in a production environment without 
                implementing appropriate additional security and privacy controls.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="cta-section">
            <a href="https://github.com/michaelsrichter/azure-elastic-risk-agent" target="_blank" class="cta-button">
                View Source Code
            </a>
            <a href="/" class="cta-button secondary">
                Back to Platform
            </a>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
